---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Add results" subtitle="Paste a results URL and we'll pull in the data.">
	<div class="card coming-soon">
		<h2>Coming next</h2>
		<p class="muted">
			This is where you'll paste a race-results link. The app will fetch the page, use Claude to
			extract names, times, and splits, then show you a preview to confirm or fix before saving —
			capturing your family's results plus the podium and nearby finishers for context.
		</p>
		<p class="muted">
			This screen (and the login that gates it) gets wired up once the Supabase project is
			connected. Until then, the sample data comes from <code>supabase/seed.sql</code>.
		</p>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style>
	.coming-soon { max-width: 60ch; }
	.coming-soon h2 { margin-top: 0; font-size: 1.2rem; }
	.coming-soon code {
		background: #00000040;
		padding: 0.1rem 0.35rem;
		border-radius: 5px;
		font-size: 0.85em;
	}
</style>
